            "position": { "area": "left", "order": 1 }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "### Linux",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large", "fontWeight": "bold" },
            "position": { "area": "right" }
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "code": "# Debian/Ubuntu\nsudo apt update\nsudo apt install git gh\n\n# Verify\ngit --version\ngh --version",
            "language": "bash",
            "position": { "area": "right", "order": 1 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "macOS users: install Homebrew first, then use it to install git and gh. Linux users: apt handles it. Windows users: I strongly recommend WSL, the Windows Subsystem for Linux. We install both git for version control and gh for GitHub operations."
