      {
        "id": "git-vs-gh",
        "layout": "two-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Two CLIs: `git` vs `gh`",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xl" },
            "position": { "area": "header" }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "### `git` -- Version Control",
            "style": {
              "fontSize": "large",
              "fontWeight": "bold",
              "color": "#F97316"
            },
            "position": { "area": "left" }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              "Tracks file changes locally",
              "Commits, branches, merges",
              "Push/pull to any remote",
              "Works without GitHub"
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "medium" },
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade", "index": 0 },
            "position": { "area": "left", "order": 1 }
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "code": "git add .\ngit commit -m \"update\"\ngit push\ngit log\ngit diff\ngit clone <url>",
            "language": "bash",
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade", "index": 2 },
            "position": { "area": "left", "order": 2 }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "### `gh` -- GitHub CLI",
            "style": {
              "fontSize": "large",
              "fontWeight": "bold",
              "color": "#2563EB"
            },
            "position": { "area": "right" }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              "Interacts with GitHub features",
              "Issues, PRs, Actions, releases",
              "Repo creation and management",
              "Requires a GitHub account"
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "medium" },
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade", "index": 1 },
            "position": { "area": "right", "order": 1 }
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "code": "gh issue create\ngh pr create\ngh repo create\ngh issue develop 42\ngh pr view\ngh repo clone user/repo",
            "language": "bash",
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade", "index": 3 },
            "position": { "area": "right", "order": 2 }
          },
          {
            "type": "callout",
            "calloutType": "info",
            "content": "**Where they overlap:** cloning repos (`git clone` vs `gh repo clone`). That is about it. You will use both together: `git` for version control, `gh` for GitHub operations.",
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "slide-up", "index": 4 },
            "position": { "area": "footer" }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "You will hear me mention two command-line tools that sound similar. git is the version control tool: it tracks changes, makes commits, manages branches. It works with any remote, not just GitHub. gh is the GitHub CLI: it handles GitHub-specific things like issues, pull requests, and repo management. The only real overlap is cloning repos; both can do it. In practice, you use them together: git for your code history, gh for your project management."
      },
      {
        "id": "branches",
        "layout": "single-column",
        "transition": "slide",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "## Branches: Safe Experimentation",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xl" },
            "position": { "area": "header" }
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "src": "./assets/icons/git-branch-flow.svg",
            "alt": "Git branching diagram showing main branch with feature branch diverging and merging back",
            "width": "90%",
            "height": "auto",
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade", "index": 0 },
            "position": { "area": "content" }
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "code": "# Create a branch and switch to it\ngit checkout -b feature/add-bandpass-filter\n\n# Do your work, commit as usual\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"feat: add 1-40 Hz bandpass filter\"\n\n# When done, push and create a pull request\ngit push -u origin feature/add-bandpass-filter",
            "language": "bash",
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade", "index": 1 },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 1 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "Branches let you experiment safely. Create a branch, do your work, and if it works, merge it back. If it doesn't, delete the branch. No harm done. This is especially important when AI is generating code; you always want an escape hatch."
      },
