            "content": "## Pull Requests: Your Review Checkpoint",
            "style": { "fontSize": "xl" },
            "position": { "area": "header" }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "A pull request (PR) is a proposal to merge changes. Even for solo work, PRs create a **checkpoint** where you review what changed.",
            "style": { "fontSize": "medium" },
            "position": { "area": "content" }
          },
          {
            "type": "bullets",
            "items": [
              "**Title:** What did you do? (<70 characters)",
              "**Description:** Why? Link to the issue",
              "**Diff:** See every line that changed",
              "**Review:** AI agents can review your PR automatically (week 3+)"
            ],
            "bulletStyle": "disc",
            "style": { "fontSize": "large" },
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "fade" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 1 }
          },
          {
            "type": "callout",
            "calloutType": "important",
            "content": "PRs are where **checks and balances** happen. This is the controlled toolbox in action.",
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "slide-up" },
            "position": { "area": "footer" }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "Pull requests are the review checkpoint. Even if you work alone, PRs force you to review what changed before it goes into main. And starting in week 3, we'll have AI agents reviewing our PRs automatically. This is the checks and balances in practice."
      },
