            "code": "# Create an issue from the terminal\ngh issue create --title \"Add bandpass filter to preprocessing\"\n\n# Create a branch from the issue\ngh issue develop 42",
            "language": "bash",
            "caption": "Using the gh CLI",
            "animation": { "fragment": true, "type": "slide-up" },
            "position": { "area": "content", "order": 1 }
          }
        ],
        "speakerNotes": "Issues are how you track work. Every significant task starts as an issue. The branch links to the issue, the PR closes the issue. It creates a complete trail from 'we need this' to 'it's done and reviewed.'"
